Courtesy photoVasquez, a Democrat, submitted his resignation in a letter to County Commission Chair Ben Rawson.
(Read Vasquez’s resignation letter here.)
“Thus, I am resigning from the County Commission effective immediately.”Vasquez has often berated people — most often women — on social media since he was elected in 2016.
That activist, Johana Bencomo, filed a formal complaint with the county commission.
“She has ruined my career, my name, and hurt my marriage over allegations for which she has refused to provide any basis,” Vasquez wrote.